()4️⃣ Link
Link link:-Link – identity ka connection kisi application ke account se,
Kya hai: Ye ek account ko represent karta hai jo kisi application me identity ke saath linked hai.
Iske through hum entitlements aur attributes track karte hain.

📦 Link ke andar kya hota hai?
Ek Link object me ye important cheeze hoti hain 👇

1️⃣ Application info:-
👉 Kis application ka account hai
Example: AD, SAP

2️⃣ Native Identity:-
👉 Account ka username
Example:-
rahul123

3️⃣ Attributes (sabse important 🔥):-
👉 Account ke sare details yahi store hote hain
Example:-
email = rahul@gmail.com
department = IT
title = Developer

4️⃣ Entitlements:-
👉 User ke paas kya access hai
Example:-
AD group
SAP role

5️⃣ Status:-
👉 Account enabled hai ya disabled
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()link object dikhta kaisa hai?teen format deta hu:-
---------------------------------------------------
🧾 1️⃣ Java Debug Print (Real Feel Output):-
Link link = identity.getLinks().get(0);

System.out.println("===== LINK OBJECT =====");
System.out.println("ID: " + link.getId());
System.out.println("Application: " + link.getApplicationName());
System.out.println("Native Identity: " + link.getNativeIdentity());
System.out.println("Instance: " + link.getInstance());
System.out.println("Disabled: " + link.isDisabled());
System.out.println("Created: " + link.getCreated());
System.out.println("Modified: " + link.getModified());

System.out.println("---- ATTRIBUTES ----");
Attributes attrs = link.getAttributes();
for (String key : attrs.getKeys()) {
    System.out.println(key + " = " + attrs.get(key));
}
