🧾 2️⃣ XML Format (🔥 Most Important – Real SailPoint Structure):-
Ye exactly waise hi dikhta hai jaise IdentityIQ DB / export me milta hai:-

<Link id="c1234567890" application="Active Directory">
    <NativeIdentity>rahul123</NativeIdentity>
    <Instance>AD_Instance</Instance>
    <Disabled>false</Disabled>
    <Attributes>
        <Map>
            <entry key="cn" value="Rahul Kumar"/>
            <entry key="mail" value="rahul@gmail.com"/>
            <entry key="department" value="IT"/>
            <entry key="title" value="Software Engineer"/>
            <entry key="memberOf">
                <List>
                    <String>CN=Admins,OU=Groups,DC=company,DC=com</String>
                    <String>CN=Users,OU=Groups,DC=company,DC=com</String>
                </List>
            </entry>
        </Map>
    </Attributes>

</Link>
/////////////*
()🔹 1️⃣ <Link id="c1234567890" application="Active Directory">:-
👉 <Link>
Ye main object tag hai
Matlab: “ye ek account (link) object hai”
👉 id="c1234567890"
Ye unique ID hai (database primary key 🔥)
Har link ka ID alag hota hai
Backend me isi se object identify hota hai
👉 application="Active Directory"
Ye batata hai:
👉 Ye account kis application ka hai
Example:-
Active Directory
SAP
Database

🔹 2️⃣ <NativeIdentity>rahul123</NativeIdentity>:-
👉 NativeIdentity
Ye username / login ID hota hai
Jo actual application me use hota hai
👉 Example:-
AD me: rahul123
SAP me: EMP001

🔹 4️⃣ <Disabled>false</Disabled>:-
👉 Disabled
Account ka status:-
Value	    Meaning
false	Account active hai ✅

🔹 5️⃣ <Attributes>:-
👉 🔥 Sabse important block
Yaha account ka pura data store hota hai
Ye basically ek Map (key-value) structure hai

🔹 6️⃣ <Map>:-
👉 Java ke Map jaisa:-
key → value

🔹 1️⃣ <Instance>AD_Instance</Instance>:-
👉 Ye kya hai?
Ye application ka environment / instance name hai
🧠 Simple samajh:-
Same application ke multiple versions ho sakte hain:-
Instance	     Meaning
AD_Prod:------Production server
AD_Test:------Testing server
AD_Instance:---Generic ya configured naam
🔥 Real use:-
link.getInstance();

👉 Output:-
AD_Instance
🎯 Meaning:-
👉 Ye batata hai account kis specific server ya environment me hai.
-----------------------------------------------------------
()🔹 1️⃣ entry, key, value kya hota hai?
🧠 Basic concept:-
SailPoint me Attributes = Map (Dictionary) hota hai.

👉 Map matlab:-
key → value

🔥 Real life example:-
name → Rahul
age → 25
city → Delhi

🔧 XML me kaise likhte hain?
<entry key="name" value="Rahul"/>

🧠 Breakdown:-
Word	       Meaning
entry:-------ek record (ek data item)
key	naam:----(identifier)
value:-------actual data

🎯 Simple line:-
👉 entry = key + value ka pair.
--------------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ Example (Simple entry):-
<entry key="cn" value="Rahul Kumar"/>
👉 Matlab:-
cn → Rahul Kumar
👉 Java me:-
attributes.put("cn", "Rahul Kumar");
-----------------------------------------------
🔥 3️⃣ Ab main part — memberOf:-
<entry key="memberOf">
    <List>
        <String>CN=Admins,OU=Groups,DC=company,DC=com</String>
        <String>CN=Users,OU=Groups,DC=company,DC=com</String>
    </List>
</entry>

🔸 STEP 2: value kaha hai? 🤔
👉 Yaha value="..." nahi hai
👉 Kyunki value ek nahi hai ❌
👉 Multiple values hain ✅
➡️ Isliye <List> use hua hai

🔸 STEP 3: <List>:-
👉 Matlab:-
value = list (multiple items)
👉 Java me:-
List<String> groups;

()🔹 1️⃣ entry key="memberOf":-
👉 Ye kya karta hai?
<entry key="memberOf">
👉 Iska matlab:-
"memberOf" naam ka ek field hai.

()🔹 <String>CN=Admins,OU=Groups,DC=company,DC=com</String>
👉 Ye exactly kya hai?

👉 Ye ek DN (Distinguished Name) hai
➡️ Matlab: LDAP / Active Directory me kisi object ka full address

🧠 Simple analogy (real life):-
👉 Jaise address hota hai:-
House No → Street → City → Country

👉 Waise hi ye DN hai:-
CN → OU → DC → DC

🔍 Full Breakdown (deep understanding):-
CN=Admins,OU=Groups,DC=company,DC=com

🔸 1️⃣ CN=Admins:-
👉 CN = Common Name
👉 Ye actual group ka naam hai
✅ IMPORTANT:-
👉 Ye hi main cheez hai jo use hoti hai
Group Name = Admins

🔸 2️⃣ OU=Groups:-
👉 OU = Organizational Unit
👉 Matlab:-
➡️ Ye group kis folder me rakha hai
Folder = Groups

🔸 3️⃣ DC=company:-
👉 DC = Domain Component
👉 Domain ka part

🔸 4️⃣ DC=com:-
👉 Domain ka last part

🔥 Combine karke:-
Admins group → Groups folder → company.com domain
🎯 Final Meaning:-
👉 Ye line bol rahi hai:-
"User Admins group ka member hai jo company.com domain ke Groups folder me hai"
