🔹 toMap():-
👉 Object ko Map (key-value format) me convert karta hai
📌 Use:-
Debugging
Logging
Data transfer

🔹 fromMap(Map):-
👉 Map se data lekar object me set karta hai
📌 Use:-
Data restore karna
API se data load karna

🔹 toXml():-
👉 Object ko XML format me convert karta hai
📌 Use:-
Export
Config save
SailPoint XML structure

🔹 fromXml(String xml):-
👉 XML se data lekar object me convert karta hai
📌 Use:-
Import
Configuration load
Object recreate

✅ Code Example (Without * import)
import sailpoint.object.Link;
import java.util.Map;
import java.util.HashMap;

public class LinkConvertExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Link link = new Link();

        // Basic data set
        link.setDisplayName("Kishan Account");
        link.setNativeIdentity("kishan.ad");

        // =========================
        // 🔹 toMap
        // =========================
        Map map = link.toMap();
        System.out.println("Map Output: " + map);

        // =========================
        // 🔹 fromMap
        // =========================
        Link newLink = new Link();
        newLink.fromMap(map);
        System.out.println("FromMap DisplayName: " + newLink.getDisplayName());

        // =========================
        // 🔹 toXml
        // =========================
        String xml = link.toXml();
        System.out.println("XML Output: " + xml);

        // =========================
        // 🔹 fromXml
        // =========================
        Link xmlLink = new Link();
        xmlLink.fromXml(xml);
        System.out.println("FromXml DisplayName: " + xmlLink.getDisplayName());
    }
}
✅ Output (Simplified):-
Map Output: {displayName=Kishan Account, nativeIdentity=kishan.ad}

FromMap DisplayName: Kishan Account

XML Output: <Link>
              <DisplayName>Kishan Account</DisplayName>
              <NativeIdentity>kishan.ad</NativeIdentity>
            </Link>

FromXml DisplayName: Kishan Account
